        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(anthropic): merge consecutive assistant turns in turn validation",
        "body": "## Description\n\nFixes #87329 (RC-2)\n\nAnthropic API strictly requires alternating user/assistant message turns. When subagent announce-delivery writes echo messages that inherit the original API response metadata (`provider=\"anthropic\"`), they bypass the `isTranscriptOnlyOpenClawAssistantMessage` filter and appear as real consecutive assistant turns. This causes Anthropic to reject every subsequent request with:\n\n```\nthinking or redacted_thinking blocks in the latest assistant message cannot be modified.\n```\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`validateAnthropicTurns` only merges consecutive user turns — it never merges consecutive assistant turns. The `validateGeminiTurns` path already uses `mergeConsecutiveAssistantTurns` for this exact scenario, but the Anthropic path was never updated to include it.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdded assistant-turn merging to `validateAnthropicTurns` using the existing `mergeConsecutiveAssistantTurns` helper (already proven in the Gemini path):\n\n1. First strip dangling tool uses (existing behavior)\n2. Merge consecutive assistant turns (new — matches Gemini behavior)\n3. Merge consecutive user turns (existing behavior)\n\n## Testing\n\n- Existing Anthropic turn validation tests continue to pass\n- Consecutive echo assistant messages are now silently merged before being sent to the Anthropic API, preventing the \"cannot be modified\" error\n",
        "branch": "fix/anthropic-assistant-merge",
